name: r-ttdo
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.0.8' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ttdo
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ttdo_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ttdo/ttdo_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 635528f0353435b5f597ef1b8824a4fb6166daf10c71612292c378d2727599a0

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-diffobj
    - r-tinytest >=1.3.1
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-diffobj
    - r-tinytest >=1.3.1

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ttdo')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ttdo')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/eddelbuettel/ttdo/, https://dirk.eddelbuettel.com/code/ttdo.html
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: The 'tinytest' package offers a light-weight zero-dependency unit-testing framework
    to which this package adds support of the 'diffobj' package for 'diff'-style comparison
    of R objects.
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - jdblischak

# Package: ttdo
# Title: Extend 'tinytest' with 'diffobj'
# Version: 0.0.8
# Date: 2021-07-17
# Author: Dirk Eddelbuettel and Alton Barbehenn
# Maintainer: Dirk Eddelbuettel <edd@debian.org>
# Description: The 'tinytest' package offers a light-weight zero-dependency unit-testing framework to which this package adds support of the 'diffobj' package for 'diff'-style comparison of R objects.
